<br>
My question for the high-level beastmasters on FV out there, Lyonn, Sheerz, Krobic (and maybe a few more?) is whether or not they're welcome on all raids / high-level exp groups. <br>
<br>
The reason I'm asking this on FV boards rather than on BST forums is that the low population plus the overall more &quot;friendly&quot; atmosphere on our server might be a factor in this. I know getting into groups is not a problem for high-level beastmasters on FV unlike other servers, I have very fond memories of hunting with Sheerz myself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Also recall seeing (and being surprised at) Krobic with his warder on a Hate raid. <br>
<br>
Any insights regarding this issue would be much appreciated, can a beastmaster easily find a place in any group from NToV to Old Seb or are there certain places that might be considered off-limits (at least for your warder) ? I might resume playing this character once I'm back in Istanbul.<br>
<br>
Cyth<br>
<br>
PS: A more general question about roleplaying a beastmaster; do you all assume that your warder is a magical creature that's summoned as the VI kinda dictates or are there any &quot;tamers&quot; out there? Personally, I find the concept of a barbarian tamer of wild beasts more appealing. Not sure where all those shaman powers come from however <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucythilix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cythilix</A> at: 5/17/02 2:38:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 658<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/17/02 2:54:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=85.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A question for high-level beastmasters </span><hr size=1> From what I've seen, they are welcome, but no pets are allowed so they are a weak monk / shaman combination in a raid situation... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/17/02 3:28:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=85.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> On SH ..</span><hr size=1> .. Beasts are great for xp -- everyone loves them for that.  They're just tolerated for raids.  The only thing they do for a raid is add to the lag.  SH isn't FV, but it's similar in population. <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
<i>"Mmmmm, fissssh!  You musst fillet thiss carefully!"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urhatha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhatha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Khati Sha</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/18/02 3:08:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=85.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://darklance.freewebspace.com/images/rhatha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: On SH ..</span><hr size=1> Check out www.eqbeastlord.com for info from servers across the board.  General concensus seems to be, for most raids, pets are okay with proper control, but AOE heavy areas and other factors can lead to disallowing pets.  The biggest advantage a beastlord has here is the ability to click an icon and unsummon the warder, hopefully before it careens into a group of foes.<br>
<br>
I have very little personal experience here... I was on a Naggy raid and was allowed to have my warder up the whole time, though that seemed to be a dungeon that really had no pathing/aoe problems.<br>
<br>
As for pets breaking mez and the effect on raids, that can often be prevented by periodically backing off the pet and sending him/her/it again mid fight, clering aggro from any things that may have hit you before mez, or broken it for a second and taken a swing.  I haven't grouped with enchanters enough to truly say this will prevent all issues, but the times I've had to use it, it's worked rather well. <p>-----------------------------<BR><A HREF='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112438' target=new>Rhatha Sha`Naya</A> and Swiftclaw <BR>
