<I>In loving memory of Dazzani</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukelisk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelisk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No, YOU'RE evil</span><br>  Posts: 330<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/18/02 11:11:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=85.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: On SH ..</span><hr size=1> We're awesome in EXP groups--Need a warrior? Call your friendly neighborhood beastlord.  Need a backup healer? Call your friendly neighborhood beastlord.  Need a distracter while you evacuate? Call...you get the picture.<br>
<br>
As for raids, on a lot of them people demand that NO PETS are summoned. That basically makes us level 40 shaman at level 60--not much use.<br>
