the most useful class in a raid situation, but perhaps we will get some decent AA skills one of these days which will help with that game aspect.<br>
<br>
Beastlords have desireable abilities in my opinion:<br>
- good pet (great for soloing or parking adds)<br>
- great pet heals<br>
- sow<br>
- invis<br>
- block (better than parry)<br>
- dual wield (one of my favorite skills)<br>
- slow (you would be surprised how much 30% helps)<br>
- disease dot (stops hp regen of npcs, and great for getting aggro (if you need to))<br>
- chloroplast<br>
- stonestance disc (bst's call it protective spirit, a true life saver)<br>
- mana regen at 59 (wish we had a lower level one)<br>
- dex\sta buffs when no shaman around<br>
<br>
I am very happy with the class and enjoy it a lot, even though we don't play much of a role in raids atm.  Aside from the raid role, I do wish we had a rooting ability (aside from weapon procs).  I don't think we will ever get it, but it is a nice dream  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
For example, I was soloing in velks the other day, positioned near the right corner and was fighting a single spider.  pretty easy.  Well, a soloing warrior decided to plop two more spiders on me.  Now all three spiders were on my pet, and I was running low on mana.  I healed the pet once, had him switch targets to a new spider briefly, and then slowed the two new spiders.  The one spider that did not have time for pet to build aggro got on me, I then got on the first spider and had my pet switch back to him and we finished him off.  I threw up stonestance to help soak damage, and assisting my pet started work on the second spider.  Well my pet was getting close to death, and I was oom and near death myself.  In the end I had to zone.  If we had root, I could have simply pulled the adds to me with slow, root parked them, and ran back to the pet to kill his mob.  <br>
<br>
We do really well one-on-one, but with adds beastlords need to make some quick choices.  Two mobs aren't that bad, but when we get to 3+ it gets interesting  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Zokof<br>
